      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>When a single alkene monomer, such as ethylene, is polymerized, the product is a <i>homopolymer.</i> If a mixture of two alkene monomers is polymerized, however, a <i>copolymer</i> often results. The following structure represents a segment of a copolymer called <i>Saran.</i> What two monomers were copolymerized to make Saran?</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBcUFTIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--ecaa465fbb6b8c02d1d65d9aaec6f2a18a8ff215/OChem_08_EC_044.jpg\" alt=\"Saran is a copolymer with a repeating  4-carbon chain containing two chlorine atoms bonded to C2  bonded and one chlorine atom bonded to C4.\">",
